The paper presents a logic-based approach to debugging Java programs, which involves representing program execution as a logic database and implementing queries as logic programs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category, as it deals with a methodology for debugging software. Additionally, the use of logic programming and databases suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. The paper's focus on answering queries about program execution also suggests that it may be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of databases and queries suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category.
